metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #807
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Resilience  #67
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

metadata.name: Pobbles #284
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
‚Ä¢ They work well with toddlers.

metadata.name: Tails of Majestic Creatures #123
metadata.description:
Excerpt from the Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

"Some of the fantastically colored reeds that grow in clumps along the banks of the Tezonian river have profoundly affected the local inhabitants' culture, and beliefs.

Legend tells of how there lived majestic creatures, that were so beautiful, and dazzling, that they greatly offended Nocturna - the Deity of the Night. After many unsuccessful attempts to get rid of them, usually foiled by the clever Majestic Creatures in elaborate ways, Nocturna cast a powerful spell upon them. This spell was extremely effective and made the Majestic Creatures plummet, with great speed, into the ground leaving only their tails to show.

The creatures then turned their energy to nature, and joined as one to become a deity of the natural world. They rise, and protect creatures from harm, especially during the night.

The reeds (tails) are held as sacred, and believed to have healing powers.

I have created this graphical study of the tails (exotic reeds) for your informational requirements and ocular interest.

128 images are planned to follow henceforth, subject to available minters."

s will save a 4000x4000 jpg of the image. 
g will convert to gray.
c will convert back to color.
m will save a 4000x4000 monochrome jpg of the image.

Coded in P5.js

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #178
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #88
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.description:
The third dazzle project, this time we see a sunrise, obscured by the dazzle pattern.

This project has been interesting to complete, there's a tension in hiding the beauty of a simple sunrise, reflecting the barriers we come across and set for ourselves.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #227
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: Pebbles #49
metadata.description:
Generative series in six different ranges of 30 colors each that are combined with 150 colors forming a wall. "The Pebbles" series pays tribute to these first ancestral wall constructions in dry stone without concrete to hold them together. It is an ancient technique that dates back to the Stone Age.

This series of generatives NFTs is born from the drawings presented in Milan at the Galer√≠a Patricia Armocida. They are composed of stone blocks in 6 series of 50 originals in which 30 colors per range are combined with 150 secondary range colors in infinite shapes.

http://www.nuriamora.com/serie-piedras/

The second Range is Red.

Previous Series:
Serie 1 Blue: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/pebbles

Coded in P5js.

Source code based on Roni Kaufman previous work and used under a collaborative agreement.
